

---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Article from "../../components/Article.astro";
---

<Layout title="synchronicity">
  <Article
    title="synchronicity"
    section="mysticism"
    updated="archive draft"
  >
    <p>
      synchronicity is the experience of meaningful coincidence—events that
      align in a way that feels connected, even when no direct cause can be
      identified.
    </p>

    <p>
      something happens in the outer world that mirrors an inner state, thought,
      or question. the connection is not mechanical, but symbolic.
    </p>

    <p>
      because of this, synchronicity often feels charged, as if something is
      being revealed through the alignment itself.
    </p>

    <h2>coincidence and meaning</h2>

    <p>
      ordinary coincidence becomes synchronicity when it carries significance.
      the event is not just noticed—it feels directed, as if it belongs to a
      larger pattern.
    </p>

    <p>
      the meaning does not come from proof, but from the quality of the
      experience.
    </p>

    <h2>inner and outer</h2>

    <p>
      synchronicity links inner and outer events. a thought, image, or feeling
      appears internally, and something corresponding appears externally.
    </p>

    <p>
      this creates the sense that reality is not entirely separate from the
      psyche.
    </p>

    <h2>interpretation</h2>

    <p>
      not every coincidence is meaningful. interpretation requires care. it is
      easy to project patterns where none exist.
    </p>

    <p>
      at the same time, dismissing all meaning removes something real from
      experience. synchronicity exists in the tension between skepticism and
      openness.
    </p>

    <div class="mini-links">
      <a class="link-blue" href="/mysticism">back to mysticism index</a>
      <a class="link-blue" href="/mysticism/vision">continue to: vision</a>
      <a class="link-red" href="/mysticism/hidden-meaning">hidden meaning</a>
    </div>
  </Article>
</Layout>